 "then behold, a bright cloud overshadowed them,

259
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:55,920
 "and a voice in the cloud said,

260
00:10:55,920 --> 00:10:59,560
 "This is my beloved son with whom I am well pleased.

261
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:01,760
 "Listen to him."

262
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:05,600
 By the way, that's Hebrew for, "Shut up."

263
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:09,400
 Listen, it's really hard to hear from the Lord

264
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,480
 when you're doing all the talking.

265
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,520
 You ever notice that?

266
00:11:11,520 --> 00:11:13,840
 You ever have some thing in your life,

267
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:16,000
 you're like, "I just need to pray about it."

268
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,200
 And then you do all the talking?

269
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,600
 'Cause sometimes we pray like idiots.

270
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:20,760
 You ever know this?

271
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:22,720
 You just start informing God of all the details.

272
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:24,920
 "Hey, God, I don't know if you're aware of this,

273
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,200
 "the Dow Jones is down."

274
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,720
 He's like, "Yeah, I know."

275
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:29,920
 And we just talk and talk and talk and talk,

276
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:32,600
 and Peter just will not be quiet.

277
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:36,800
 And then God the Father shows up and he says,

278
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:39,800
 "Hey, man, listen to him."

279
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,200
 Verse six, "And when the disciples heard this,

280
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,400
 "they fell on their face and they were terrified."

281
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:46,480
 And if I had time to go through it,

282
00:11:46,480 --> 00:11:47,840
 I would let you know that Matthew

283
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,160
 is writing to a Jewish audience.

284
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:51,760
 Matthew is trying to help his Jewish readers

285
00:11:51,760 --> 00:11:53,800
 understand that Jesus is the greater Israel,

286
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,600
 Jesus is the greater Moses.

287
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:57,320
 And if you go back to Exodus 19 and 20,

288
00:11:57,320 --> 00:11:58,960
 Moses goes up, he waits six days,

289
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,600
 he goes up on to Mount Sinai,

290
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:02,320
 three named people go up with him.

291
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,480
 But God said, "You gotta concentrate yourself.

292
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:06,040
 "And if you come up here on this mountain

293
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:07,520
 "where I'm gonna give the 10 commandments,

294
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:10,280
 "if you are not perfect or holy, I'm gonna kill you."

295
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:12,440
 And now Peter, James, and John are sitting there,

296
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,920
 Peter opens his dumb mouth,

297
00:12:13,920 --> 00:12:16,160
 and then God the Father shows up,

298
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:18,000
 shuts down the transfiguration,

299
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:20,880
 and they're like, "Uh-oh, we're dead men."

300
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:21,840
 They fall on their face

301
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:24,040
 'cause they think they're going to die.

302
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:30,600
 Verse seven, "But Jesus came and touched them saying,

303
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:33,680
 "Rise and have no fear."

304
00:12:33,680 --> 00:12:36,840
 You know what the most commanded thing is

305
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:37,840
 in all of the Bible?

306
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:41,120
 Fear not.

307
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,760
 In the King James version of the Bible,

308
00:12:42,760 --> 00:12:47,520
 there's at least 366 times where there's some version of,

309
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:50,760
 "Do not fear, do not be afraid, fear not,

310
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:52,200
 "be anxious for nothing."

311
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:53,040
 Why?

312
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:53,920
 Because I don't know about you,

313
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:55,320
 but every single day of my life,

314
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:58,280
 including leap year, I need to hear from God Almighty,

315
00:12:58,280 --> 00:13:00,880
 "Don't be afraid, I got you."

316
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:03,600
 But Jesus came and touched them saying,

317
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:07,240
 "Rise and have no fear."

318
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:13,560
 You see, the Bible says that this is love.

319
00:13:13,560 --> 00:13:14,640
 Not that we first loved God,

320
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:16,880
 but God first loved us and sent his Son

321
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:19,720
 as the propitiation for our sin.

322
00:13:19,720 --> 00:13:21,000
 Say propitiation.

323
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:24,280
 Say it one more time, propitiation.

324
00:13:24,280 --> 00:13:26,200
 Propitiation is the theological term

325
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:29,040
 that means a payment that satisfies.

326
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,600
 Now, when I planted our church,

327
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,600
 I was told that your generation

328
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,920
 couldn't learn theological terminology,

329
00:13:34,920 --> 00:13:36,640
 but I fully believe that if you can order

330
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:40,040
 a venti caramel macchiato, you can learn propitiation.

331
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:41,120
 Propitiation.

332
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:43,960
 Here's what it means, a payment that satisfies,

333
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:44,800
 which means this.

334
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:46,120
 Try to hang on to this for a second.

335
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:48,680
 See, some of you think God's mad at you,

336
00:13:48,680 --> 00:13:51,240
 but if you put your faith in Jesus Christ,

337
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,240
 then you have received his righteousness.

338
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:55,720
 And if Jesus is the payment that satisfies,

339
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:59,440
 this means he cannot be dissatisfied in you.

340
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:00,640
 He's not mad at you.

341
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:05,640
 He poured out his full wrath on his Son on the cross.

342
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:08,280
 And when they lifted up their eyes,

343
00:14:08,280 --> 00:14:10,160
 they saw no one but Jesus only.

344
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:11,760
 By the way, that's how you get over fear.

345
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:14,240
 You fix your eyes on Jesus.

346
00:14:14,240 --> 00:14:17,200
 And then the things of this world grow strangely dim.

347
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:19,120
 And as they were coming down the mountain

348
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:22,840
 after this incredible moment, they heard the voice of God.

349
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:26,960
 They saw Jesus in a transfigured, glorified state.

350
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:27,800
 They saw Moses.

351
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:28,680
 They saw Elijah.

352
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:30,360
 This is a mountaintop moment.

353
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:32,240
 And as they were coming down the mountain,

354
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:34,480
 Jesus commanded them, tell no one the vision

355
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:37,240
 until the Son of Man has raised from the dead.

356
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:39,600
 For the rest of the chapter, he explains the gospel to 'em,

357
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:42,400
 and he basically says, keep this to yourself 'til Easter,

358
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:44,800
 and then after Easter, tell the world.

359
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:46,360
 Flip over to Mark chapter nine.

360
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:49,600
 And the only reason I wanna do this,

361
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,040
 the Bible doesn't have stories.

362
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,200
 The Bible records actual events,

363
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:57,840
 and Mark decides to share some different details

364
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,440
 about the events that happened.

365
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,600
 This is the same event.

366
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,440
 Mountain of Transfiguration.

367
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:04,400
 They're walking down the mountain.

368
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:06,400
 They're not meant to sit and soak up on the mountain

369
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:09,520
 because the ministry happens down in the valley.

370
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:10,920
 And when they get down in the valley,

371
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:11,880
 here's what they run into.

372
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:14,560
 If we'll pick it up in Mark nine, beginning in verse 14.

373
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:16,880
 It says, "And when they came to the disciples,

374
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:19,940
 "they saw a great crowd around them.

375
00:15:19,940 --> 00:15:22,480
 "And scribes arguing with them.

376
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:25,280
 "And immediately, all the crowd, when they saw him,"

377
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:27,000
 that's Jesus, "they were greatly amazed,

378
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:30,120
 "and they ran up to him, and they greeted him.

379
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:32,720
 "And he," being Jesus, "asked them,

380
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:35,400
 "what are you arguing about with them?

381
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:38,140
 "And they don't answer, 'cause they know they're in trouble.

382
00:15:38,140 --> 00:15:41,680
 "And someone from the crowd answered him,

383
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:44,840
 "Teacher, I brought my son to you,

384
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:47,200
 "for he has a spirit that makes him mute,

385
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:50,160
 "and whenever it seizes him, it throws him down,

386
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:51,920
 "and he foams, and he grinds his teeth,

387
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:55,120
 "and he becomes rigid, and so I ask your disciples

388
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:56,960
 "to cast it out.'

389
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:58,280
 "And they were not able."

390
00:15:58,280 --> 00:16:00,960
 Now again, man, if you grew up in church,

391
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,400
 you already know the way this thing ends,

392
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:04,720
 but I don't want you to run to the end too quickly,

393
00:16:04,720 --> 00:16:06,880
 and I don't want you to think about this as a story,

394
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,140
 'cause it's not a story.

395
00:16:08,140 --> 00:16:11,200
 It's not, this is an actual event.

396
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:15,680
 Like this is a real dad, with a real name,

397
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,680
 and a permanent address, and he had a job,

398
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:19,780
 and he had a wife, and he's got a kid,

399
00:16:19,780 --> 00:16:24,000
 and he's got some serious kid pain.

400
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:27,600
 And you just kind of have to trust me on this one.

401
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:29,980
 If you're a parent, you know what I'm talking about.

402
00:16:29,980 --> 00:16:31,880
 But there ain't no pain like kid pain.

403
00:16:31,880 --> 00:16:34,240
 There ain't no pain like kid pain.

404
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,880
 I don't know how to describe it,

405
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,680
 but the reason there's no pain like kid pain

406
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:40,060
 is 'cause there's no love like kid love.

407
00:16:40,060 --> 00:16:41,280
 I'm just telling you, I've been married

408
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:44,060
 to Gretchen right here for 26 years.

409
00:16:44,060 --> 00:16:45,400
 If you look at her and you look at me,

410
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,760
 you will know that James was right,

411
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:48,780
 and when he said, "The prayers of a righteous man

412
00:16:48,780 --> 00:16:51,020
 "availeth much," by God.

413
00:16:51,020 --> 00:16:54,040
 And so, that means she's way better looking to me, all right?

414
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:55,920
 And I love her so much, and if I tell her too much,

415
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:58,160
 I'll get all weepy-eyed, and my chin will shake,

416
00:16:58,160 --> 00:16:59,740
 and whatever, and I love her.

417
00:16:59,740 --> 00:17:02,020
 But when we found out we were having babies,

418
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:04,700
 oh my God, one of the happiest days of my whole life.

419
00:17:04,700 --> 00:17:05,920
 We were pregnant, mostly her,

420
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:07,840
 but I would go to all the meetings, all right?

421
00:17:07,840 --> 00:17:10,080
 (congregation laughing)

422
00:17:10,080 --> 00:17:12,080
 And we go to this one, I can't remember

423
00:17:12,080 --> 00:17:13,760
 how many weeks in it is, and all that stuff,

424
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:15,440
 but we go to the doctor where you find out

425
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:17,560
 the sex of the child, oof.

426
00:17:17,560 --> 00:17:20,280
 And so, I go in there, and they lay her on the table,

427
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:22,120
 and they put that goopy stuff on the belly, man,

428
00:17:22,120 --> 00:17:23,680
 and they got this little magic wand,

429
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,080
 and go, "Whoa," you know?

430
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:26,720
 And you're looking at a TV.

431
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:28,920
 And I'm in there just staring at that thing.

432
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:29,960
 She's like, "What do you see?"

433
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,200
 And I'm like, "Baby, it don't look good.

434
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,320
 "I think we're having E.T.

435
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:34,320
 "This don't look, it looks like a gummy bear.

436
00:17:34,320 --> 00:17:35,160
 "It's terrible."

437
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:38,840
 And then, the little doctor, this little lady was a doctor,

438
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:40,040
 she was, you know, whatever, this lady,

439
00:17:40,040 --> 00:17:41,300
 she's about this tall, and she goes,

440
00:17:41,300 --> 00:17:44,800
 "Congratulations, Mr. Martin, it's a boy."

441
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,800
 And dude, I got so excited, I scooped her up.

442
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,400
 I picked her up off the ground.

443
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,240
 Gradually said, "Put her down."

444
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:50,880
 So I put her down.

445
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:53,320
 I was so pumped, man, to have a boy.

446
00:17:53,320 --> 00:17:56,280
 I called my daddy, I said, "Daddy, I made a boy."

447
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:57,200
 That's what I said.

448
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:59,040
 You know what he said?

449
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:00,160
 "Son, I knew you had it in you."

450
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:01,240
 That's what he said back.

451
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:04,240
 (audience laughing)

452
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:07,800
 And then, it's the day of the delivery.

453
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:09,680
 It's not awesome.

454
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:10,760
 Don't let 'em lie to you.

455
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:12,200
 It's a little bit of a train wreck,

456
00:18:12,200 --> 00:18:15,160
 but you're not ready for it, but whatever.

457
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:17,560
 So, when all that stuff was over,

458
00:18:17,560 --> 00:18:19,720
 and they wrapped up that little thing, man.

459
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:22,560
 I named him, I named him after me.

460
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,160
 I'm the third, Joseph A. Martin III.

461
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:25,040
 My dad's junior.

462
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:26,200
 I was almost junior, junior.

463
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:27,600
 That happens where I'm from.

464
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:28,720
 And so, I named him the fourth.

465
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:30,920
 We're into me at my house, at least I am.

466
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:32,920
 And they wrap him up in that little burrito of love,

467
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,880
 and they hand you your little kid, man.

468
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:39,080
 And you look at him, and you think, "Oh, my goodness."

469
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:40,720
 I mean, it's actually a reflection

470
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:42,720
 of the character and nature of God,

471
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:46,640
 that God joined me and Gretchen together as one,

472
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,940
 and out of an overflow of our love for one another.

473
00:18:48,940 --> 00:18:50,760
 We have image bearers.

474
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:51,800
 Like, this happened.

475
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:55,560
 And then, I just, I looked at him, and he had a skullet.

476
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:57,000
 You know what a skullet is?

477
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,600
 It's like, bald on top, mullet in the back.

478
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:00,880
 You can tell I'm from the country,

479
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:02,560
 and I was like, "You can take the boy out of the country,

480
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:04,360
 "but look at mine, son, look."

481
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:06,620
 (audience laughing)

482
00:19:06,620 --> 00:19:08,800
 Four years later, we find out we're pregnant again.

483
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:11,440
 Again, mostly Gretchen, but I went to all the meetings.

484
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:14,160
 And we're back at the little doctor lady's office

485
00:19:14,160 --> 00:19:15,340
 with the goopy stuff on there.

486
00:19:15,340 --> 00:19:17,520
 Whoa, doing the thing, you know?

487
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:21,200
 And she said, "Congratulations, Mr. Martin, it's a girl."

488
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,520
 And I went, "All right."

489
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:23,600
 Gretchen said, "You gonna be okay?"

490
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:25,100
 I said, "I'm gonna be okay."

491
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:27,220
 Now, listen, there's no greater thing

492
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:29,160
 than being a girl dad, okay?

493
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:31,240
 Reagan Capri, my 16-year-old, is right there.

494
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:33,600
 There's nothing on the planet like it.

495
00:19:33,600 --> 00:19:34,920
 But you just kinda got a cowboy up

496
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:36,780
 a little extra these days, all right?

497
00:19:36,780 --> 00:19:39,600
 And, girls, not 'cause of you, 'cause of these stinky things

498
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:41,560
 sitting next to you, that's the problem, amen?

499
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:45,400
 So, I'm back in the room, I know what to expect,

500
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:47,520
 so I do not go south of the top of the bed.

501
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:49,040
 Occasionally, I drop in like Spider-Man,

502
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:49,880
 like, "How you doing, baby?

503
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:50,960
 "All right, I'll be back here."

504
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:53,280
 And then, finally, Reagan Capri's here.

505
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:56,240
 By the way, she was born, she was seven pounds on the nose.

506
00:19:56,240 --> 00:20:01,240
 In the Bible, that's the number of perfection, praise God.

507
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:03,840
 And they wrap up little Reagan Capri.

508
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:06,160
 But here's the thing, here's the thing.

509
00:20:06,160 --> 00:20:09,080
 Nobody tells you this, if you have more than one kid,

510
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:10,240
 you can't ask this out loud,

511
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,900
 'cause you'll sound like a terrible human being.

512
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:15,300
 But I begin to think, "Oh, no.

513
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:17,160
 "Am I gonna be able to love the second one

514
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,320
